1
00:00:22,106 --> 00:00:23,899
<i>Don't you want this</i>
<i>to end already?</i>

2
00:00:23,983 --> 00:00:25,317
So we can finally find out
who your lover is, who the traitor is,

3
00:00:25,401 --> 00:00:26,402
and who's telling the truth?

4
00:00:26,485 --> 00:00:28,154
<i>You'll come with me</i>
<i>to the station.</i>

5
00:00:28,237 --> 00:00:29,822
<i>You'll admit</i>
<i>that everything is your fault.</i>

6
00:00:29,905 --> 00:00:33,659
<i>I want everyone to know</i>
<i>that Attorney Ace Verona almost shot me</i>

7
00:00:33,743 --> 00:00:36,620
<i>and even Ms. Gem's life</i>
<i>is in danger in his hands.</i>

8
00:00:36,704 --> 00:00:38,914
<i>His father, Judge Verona,</i>
<i>also kidnapped my father.</i>

9
00:00:38,998 --> 00:00:41,041
<i>You're also experiencing fatigue,</i>

10
00:00:41,125 --> 00:00:42,543
<i>dizziness, and nausea.</i>

11
00:00:42,626 --> 00:00:44,503
<i>But these are normal,</i>
<i>especially in this condition.</i>

12
00:00:44,587 --> 00:00:45,963
<i>Congratulations! You're pregnant!</i>

13
00:00:46,046 --> 00:00:48,340
- <i>Am I the father?</i>
- <i>We'll do a paternity test.</i>

14
00:00:48,424 --> 00:00:50,134
- What if it's mine?
- Then it's ours.

15
00:00:50,217 --> 00:00:51,135
<i>We'll run away.</i>

16
00:00:51,218 --> 00:00:52,386
What if it's not yours?

17
00:00:52,470 --> 00:00:54,388
Nothing will change.

18
00:00:55,723 --> 00:00:57,224
<i>Someone will be joining our meeting.</i>

19
00:00:57,308 --> 00:00:58,225
Hello, everyone!

20
00:00:58,309 --> 00:01:02,021
We are now positioned to move forward
to the next phase without disruption.

21
00:01:02,104 --> 00:01:05,441
♪ <i>Love is never gone... ♪</i>

22
00:01:38,432 --> 00:01:40,851
Ooh, madam!

23
00:01:41,435 --> 00:01:43,020
That's insane!

24
00:01:43,103 --> 00:01:44,730
More! More!

25
00:01:44,814 --> 00:01:46,899
Madam, please calm down!

26
00:01:46,982 --> 00:01:51,028
I just want to drown
in all of this champagne!

27
00:01:51,111 --> 00:01:54,907
And even if you add all of those tequila,

28
00:01:55,741 --> 00:02:00,704
beer, all these alcoholic drinks,
it's okay!

29
00:02:00,788 --> 00:02:02,957
Can you tell me
what's going on?

30
00:02:03,040 --> 00:02:05,543
You're ruining your flawless makeup.

31
00:02:06,085 --> 00:02:08,045
It's so easy...

32
00:02:08,796 --> 00:02:12,174
to see Ace as the villain here.

33
00:02:12,258 --> 00:02:14,718
But he's not the villain.

34
00:02:14,802 --> 00:02:17,721
You just think he is because he hurt Gem.

35
00:02:18,931 --> 00:02:21,100
But Gem cheated on him!

36
00:02:21,183 --> 00:02:24,311
With this driver! This Teo guy!

37
00:02:26,772 --> 00:02:28,482
And now, she's pregnant?

38
00:02:29,608 --> 00:02:34,113
I am 101% sure

39
00:02:34,196 --> 00:02:37,825
that that baby is not Ace's
but that Teo's!

40
00:02:44,582 --> 00:02:47,918
Sir,
there are still no results in the search

41
00:02:48,002 --> 00:02:50,504
for Tony Castellano or Guillermo Magno.

42
00:02:51,213 --> 00:02:52,381
The same goes for Diane Pineda.

43
00:02:52,464 --> 00:02:55,885
<i>However, we found someone from Ilocos</i>
<i>who shares the same name.</i>

44
00:02:56,719 --> 00:02:59,889
<i>We will verify first</i>
<i>before going to the location.</i>

45
00:03:00,848 --> 00:03:03,350
Find them, no matter what.

46
00:03:03,434 --> 00:03:04,894
Yes, Judge.

47
00:03:07,479 --> 00:03:08,355
Bad day?

48
00:03:11,066 --> 00:03:12,067


49
00:03:12,693 --> 00:03:14,778

My troublesome daughter-in-law...

50
00:03:16,488 --> 00:03:18,198
is pregnant.

51
00:03:20,451 --> 00:03:21,785
And I...

52
00:03:23,078 --> 00:03:25,623
am looking for her other man...

53
00:03:26,498 --> 00:03:29,585
who could be the father
of the child she's carrying.

54
00:03:30,753 --> 00:03:31,629
Huh?

55
00:03:32,296 --> 00:03:33,756
How could she do that?

56
00:03:34,340 --> 00:03:36,717
She and Ace are always together.

57
00:03:37,384 --> 00:03:40,262
That's why I'm waiting
for the results of the paternity test.

58
00:03:40,346 --> 00:03:43,015
That'll snap Ace out of his delusions.

59
00:03:47,186 --> 00:03:49,271
But what if it is indeed Ace's child?

60
00:04:06,038 --> 00:04:07,706
We'll accept the child.

61
00:04:07,790 --> 00:04:09,833
But I won't be able to acknowledge it.

62
00:04:09,917 --> 00:04:13,587
Too much has happened for them
to stay together like they used to.

63
00:04:14,588 --> 00:04:16,590
And Gem's fate...

64
00:04:18,092 --> 00:04:19,635
I'm still not sure.

65
00:04:19,718 --> 00:04:21,303
I understand.

66
00:04:29,812 --> 00:04:31,063


67
00:04:38,696 --> 00:04:41,281
-

68
00:04:42,825 --> 00:04:45,160
Mm? Larajean?
It's getting late.

69
00:04:45,244 --> 00:04:47,413
How's Issay? Did something happen?

70
00:04:47,496 --> 00:04:48,914
What happened is that...

71
00:04:49,665 --> 00:04:51,583
I found out...

72
00:04:51,667 --> 00:04:53,377
Ms. Gem is pregnant.

73
00:04:53,460 --> 00:04:56,922
<i>And this came from Madam Katarina herself!</i>

74
00:04:57,006 --> 00:04:58,090
What now?

75
00:04:59,049 --> 00:05:01,051
Is this why you're so obsessed with Gem?

76
00:05:02,261 --> 00:05:03,429
'Cause you're the father?

77
00:05:03,512 --> 00:05:04,555
You're drunk.

78
00:05:04,638 --> 00:05:06,515
Pfft! Whatever!

79
00:05:06,598 --> 00:05:08,308
Just answer my question!

80
00:05:08,392 --> 00:05:09,810
I don't know.

81
00:05:10,936 --> 00:05:12,354
You don't know?

82
00:05:12,438 --> 00:05:16,191
It's either "yes" or "no,"
but your answer is that you don't know?

83
00:05:17,401 --> 00:05:19,403
What? Are you saying
you could be the father?

84
00:05:19,486 --> 00:05:22,281
Larajean, you're drunk. It's best for us
to postpone this conversation.

85
00:05:22,364 --> 00:05:25,951
Tell me, are you the father?
Or is it the Tony guy?

86
00:05:27,536 --> 00:05:29,329
'Cause I'm praying

87
00:05:29,413 --> 00:05:31,707
to all the saints in the world
that it's his.

88
00:05:31,790 --> 00:05:33,751
Or maybe it's-- it's Sir Ace's!

89
00:05:34,293 --> 00:05:35,878
Please, tell me!

90
00:05:35,961 --> 00:05:37,212
I'll get going now.

91
00:05:38,547 --> 00:05:39,548


92
00:05:57,066 --> 00:05:59,485


93
00:06:30,140 --> 00:06:32,142


94
00:06:40,818 --> 00:06:41,819


95
00:06:54,706 --> 00:06:56,375


96
00:07:25,571 --> 00:07:27,823


97
00:07:29,366 --> 00:07:30,492
Hello?

98
00:07:30,576 --> 00:07:33,287
Teo! Where's Issay?

99
00:07:33,370 --> 00:07:36,623
I couldn't find her here at home.
Did she go to yours?

100
00:07:36,707 --> 00:07:38,834
Huh? But she doesn't know
where I am right now.

101
00:07:39,418 --> 00:07:41,170
That girl...

102
00:07:41,795 --> 00:07:43,755
She told me earlier

103
00:07:43,839 --> 00:07:46,049
that she wanted to get some things
from your house.

104
00:07:46,133 --> 00:07:47,426
Maybe-- maybe she went home?

105
00:07:47,509 --> 00:07:49,678
All right. I'm near our house.
I'll go take a look.

106
00:07:49,761 --> 00:07:51,346
Okay, then.

107
00:07:56,602 --> 00:07:59,104
"Teo, someone's inside our house."

108
00:08:05,694 --> 00:08:06,862
Who are you?

109
00:08:06,945 --> 00:08:08,488
Let go of me! Who are you?

110
00:08:08,572 --> 00:08:10,616
- Let go of-- Help! Somebody!
- Shut up!

111
00:08:17,331 --> 00:08:18,373
Issay?

112
00:08:21,919 --> 00:08:23,128
Help me!

113
00:08:23,212 --> 00:08:25,047
Somebody, help me! Teo!

114
00:08:25,130 --> 00:08:26,340
Come back here!

115
00:08:37,392 --> 00:08:38,518
Where's my money?

116
00:08:38,602 --> 00:08:40,854
I already told you, I don't have it!

117
00:08:40,938 --> 00:08:42,105
Oh, is that so?

118
00:09:04,294 --> 00:09:06,713
You know,
we wouldn't have to do any of this

119
00:09:07,214 --> 00:09:08,840
if you had just given me my money--

120
00:09:08,924 --> 00:09:09,967
Enough already!

121
00:10:14,406 --> 00:10:16,491
I'm already arranging
everything you'll be needing

122
00:10:16,575 --> 00:10:17,826
for your pregnancy.

123
00:10:18,452 --> 00:10:20,287
Just wait for my instructions, all right?

124
00:10:22,664 --> 00:10:23,665
Are you ready?

125
00:10:51,068 --> 00:10:52,194
What's that?

126
00:10:53,653 --> 00:10:54,613
What's that?

127
00:10:54,696 --> 00:10:56,031
This is a tracker.

128
00:10:56,114 --> 00:10:58,283
Once you attempt
to remove it, it's gonna send me an alarm.

129
00:10:58,367 --> 00:11:00,452
Don't you dare try another stunt, Gem.

130
00:11:01,286 --> 00:11:02,537
You'll be discharged tomorrow,

131
00:11:02,621 --> 00:11:04,164
and I don't want to be stressed
by all your antics.

132
00:11:31,274 --> 00:11:33,235
We'll only be
staying here temporarily, right?

133
00:11:33,318 --> 00:11:35,195
We'll return home soon, won't we?

134
00:11:35,987 --> 00:11:37,072
Yeah, Teo.

135
00:11:37,155 --> 00:11:38,573
I took a leave of absence for now.

136
00:11:38,657 --> 00:11:39,991
I can continue my studies
afterward, right?

137
00:11:40,075 --> 00:11:41,284
Yes.

138
00:11:41,368 --> 00:11:43,036
After everything's over.

139
00:11:43,120 --> 00:11:45,038
We're not only up against the Veronas.

140
00:11:45,747 --> 00:11:48,750
- Huh?
- Gem's former boss in Morocco.

141
00:11:49,209 --> 00:11:51,294
They sent one of their men here.
They're messing with me.

142
00:11:51,795 --> 00:11:53,463
He's also the one
who broke into our house.

143
00:11:53,547 --> 00:11:57,259
Maybe it's better...
if we report those to the police.

144
00:11:57,342 --> 00:11:58,844
We can't, Pa.

145
00:11:58,927 --> 00:12:00,554
He knows Gem as Yana.

146
00:12:00,637 --> 00:12:02,556
It'll be dangerous if he says anything.

147
00:12:02,639 --> 00:12:04,057
Teo?

148
00:12:05,976 --> 00:12:07,978
Teo, it's Jepoy!

149
00:12:08,520 --> 00:12:09,521
Let him in.

150
00:12:13,692 --> 00:12:14,734
Teo.

151
00:12:15,318 --> 00:12:16,445
Jepoy.

152
00:12:16,528 --> 00:12:17,362
Oh, yeah, this is Jepoy.

153
00:12:17,446 --> 00:12:20,157
Dad, I used to work with him in Morocco.

154
00:12:20,240 --> 00:12:21,700
- Jepoy, this is my father.
- Hi, I'm Jepoy.

155
00:12:21,783 --> 00:12:24,161
This is Ronnie and my sister, Issay.

156
00:12:24,244 --> 00:12:25,871
Issay.

157
00:12:27,497 --> 00:12:28,999
Good afternoon.

158
00:12:29,082 --> 00:12:30,375
And to you as well.

159
00:12:30,459 --> 00:12:32,627
Jepoy is helping me fix everything.

160
00:12:32,711 --> 00:12:35,672
He's also the one who helped me hide
from Gimo and his family.

161
00:12:35,755 --> 00:12:38,383
Oh, Teo, your new hideout...

162
00:12:38,467 --> 00:12:40,969
is ready.
It's in the fields of the nearby town.

163
00:12:41,052 --> 00:12:42,137
Thanks, Jepoy.

164
00:12:42,220 --> 00:12:44,973
We won't stay long.
Only until we can leave the country.

165
00:12:45,056 --> 00:12:47,225
Hold on. We're going overseas?

166
00:12:48,018 --> 00:12:48,852
When?

167
00:12:48,935 --> 00:12:50,479
Anytime, Dad.

168
00:12:50,562 --> 00:12:52,189
I'm preparing your
and Issay's passports.

169
00:12:52,272 --> 00:12:54,524
- You too, Ronnie. You have one, right?
- Mm.

170
00:12:54,608 --> 00:12:56,860
I want all of you to leave...

171
00:12:56,943 --> 00:12:58,445
before everything blows up.

172
00:13:05,368 --> 00:13:06,286
Here they come!

173
00:13:06,786 --> 00:13:07,871
Judge Verona,

174
00:13:07,954 --> 00:13:10,415
are Mateo Crisanto's accusations
against you true?

175
00:13:10,499 --> 00:13:12,751
How would you
counter-react to the allegations?

176
00:13:12,834 --> 00:13:14,419
Any comments on the accusation

177
00:13:14,503 --> 00:13:15,545
that you're abusing your wife?

178
00:13:15,629 --> 00:13:17,631
I already gave my counter-affidavit.

179
00:13:18,131 --> 00:13:19,466
Mateo Crisanto just has a big mouth,

180
00:13:19,549 --> 00:13:21,593
but we know what truly happened!

181
00:13:21,676 --> 00:13:23,595
What truly happened anyway, Attorney?

182
00:13:23,678 --> 00:13:25,805
It seems that Mateo Crisanto's father

183
00:13:25,889 --> 00:13:27,599
also filed charges against you
for illegal detention.

184
00:13:27,682 --> 00:13:29,893
- I just said--
- Those are all lies.

185
00:13:29,976 --> 00:13:31,353
The truth is...

186
00:13:31,436 --> 00:13:34,898
...Mateo Crisanto's father
owes us a lot of money.

187
00:13:34,981 --> 00:13:36,650
Five hundred thousand.

188
00:13:36,733 --> 00:13:38,735
They just want to intimidate us

189
00:13:38,818 --> 00:13:41,238
so that they could escape
from their obligation.

190
00:13:41,321 --> 00:13:43,198
Is there actually
someone brave enough...

191
00:13:43,281 --> 00:13:44,533
to go up against the Veronas?

192
00:13:44,616 --> 00:13:47,202
Don't be fooled by Mateo Crisanto.

193
00:13:47,285 --> 00:13:50,121
He's not as innocent as he claims to be.

194
00:13:50,205 --> 00:13:52,707
Look,
this is the only information I have

195
00:13:52,791 --> 00:13:54,459
because everything's already been deleted.

196
00:13:54,543 --> 00:13:56,461
But it's all clear.

197
00:13:56,545 --> 00:13:59,464
Mateo Crisanto was imprisoned before
in Morocco.

198
00:13:59,548 --> 00:14:02,634
He was an accessory of a robbery

199
00:14:02,717 --> 00:14:06,680
of a sheikh, that resulted
in the death of one of his people.

200
00:14:07,639 --> 00:14:09,766
Mateo Crisanto is a criminal.

201
00:14:10,433 --> 00:14:11,768
He is a dangerous person.

202
00:14:11,851 --> 00:14:13,311
- Excuse us.
- Judge!

203
00:14:13,395 --> 00:14:15,313
- What about...
- Just stay there.

204
00:14:15,397 --> 00:14:17,482
<i>Divino released a counter-affidavit</i>

205
00:14:17,566 --> 00:14:21,361
<i>in relation to the allegations</i>
<i>against him and his family.</i>

206
00:14:21,444 --> 00:14:25,865
<i>According to Divino,</i>
<i>the root of the issue stems from the debt</i>

207
00:14:25,949 --> 00:14:27,576
<i>of Teo's father to their family,</i>

208
00:14:27,659 --> 00:14:30,495
<i>which amounts to 500,000 pesos.</i>

209
00:14:30,579 --> 00:14:34,165
<i>He added that the accusations</i>
<i>are only being used</i>

210
00:14:34,249 --> 00:14:36,167
<i>to intimidate and discredit them</i>

211
00:14:36,251 --> 00:14:39,462
<i>and to avoid financial obligations.</i>

212
00:14:39,546 --> 00:14:41,923
<i>Divino also denied any involvement</i>

213
00:14:42,007 --> 00:14:44,134
<i>in the death of Daniela Ordoñez.</i>

214
00:14:44,217 --> 00:14:46,428
<i>He insisted</i>
<i>there's no sufficient evidence,</i>

215
00:14:46,511 --> 00:14:48,805
<i>and that the allegations</i>
<i>are completely baseless.</i>

216
00:14:48,888 --> 00:14:50,473
<i>According to their side,</i>

217
00:14:50,557 --> 00:14:54,477
<i>the claim that Gem Verona is being abused</i>
<i>isn't true either.</i>

218
00:14:54,561 --> 00:14:58,064
<i>They're ready to file a libel case</i>
<i>against anyone</i>

219
00:14:58,148 --> 00:15:01,192
<i>who continues to link them</i>
<i>to these accusations.</i>

220
00:15:04,779 --> 00:15:06,531
So many lies from a so-called judge.

221
00:15:06,615 --> 00:15:08,617
I only borrowed 200,000 from him.

222
00:15:08,700 --> 00:15:10,994
I've already paid 152,000.

223
00:15:11,077 --> 00:15:12,579
How did it become 500,000?

224
00:15:13,121 --> 00:15:14,456
Should I release a statement?

225
00:15:14,539 --> 00:15:16,082
I'll say I've known you for a long time,

226
00:15:16,166 --> 00:15:18,543
that we grew up together,
that you're a good person.

227
00:15:18,627 --> 00:15:20,587
I can also say you were framed in Morocco.

228
00:15:20,670 --> 00:15:23,465
Don't. The Verona family
might take away your scholarship.

229
00:15:23,548 --> 00:15:26,343
Besides, they already revealed
that I was jailed in Morocco.

230
00:15:26,426 --> 00:15:29,471
If they dig deeper
and find out that Gem is Yana,

231
00:15:29,554 --> 00:15:31,306
her life will be in danger.

232
00:15:31,973 --> 00:15:33,642
They won't find anything, Teo.

233
00:15:33,725 --> 00:15:36,144
I looked into Yana in Morocco.

234
00:15:36,227 --> 00:15:38,480
I only got limited information.
Not even photos.

235
00:15:38,563 --> 00:15:39,606
Same here.

236
00:15:40,940 --> 00:15:43,610
But they released things
we didn't know about.

237
00:15:43,693 --> 00:15:44,736
About Gimo.

238
00:15:44,819 --> 00:15:49,366
Maybe they already know that Gem is Yana.

239
00:15:51,701 --> 00:15:53,536
Teo, maybe we need Raya now.

240
00:16:11,429 --> 00:16:15,308
I'm sorry.
I should've called you the other day.

241
00:16:15,392 --> 00:16:16,601
I have news.

242
00:16:18,395 --> 00:16:20,605
Your son is here in Morocco.

243
00:16:20,689 --> 00:16:22,357
How did that happen?

244
00:16:22,440 --> 00:16:26,361
He got a job at a hotel here.

245
00:16:27,070 --> 00:16:29,155
Then he met my Yana.

246
00:16:30,448 --> 00:16:33,535
He went to the house and saw...

247
00:16:34,577 --> 00:16:36,830
<i>our picture together.</i>

248
00:16:36,913 --> 00:16:40,333
I couldn't just say I didn't know you,

249
00:16:40,417 --> 00:16:41,835
so of course, I didn't deny it.

250
00:16:43,586 --> 00:16:46,256
Hey. What should I do?

251
00:16:46,548 --> 00:16:48,633
He must not find out I'm still alive.

252
00:16:48,717 --> 00:16:51,886
And if he looks for me,
that's what you'll tell him.

253
00:16:52,554 --> 00:16:57,142
<i>Nadia,</i>
<i>I've been dead for a long time.</i>

254
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:02,480
Yana!

255
00:17:08,737 --> 00:17:09,738
Please help me.

256
00:17:10,864 --> 00:17:13,742
Help me get your son out of prison.

257
00:17:19,080 --> 00:17:20,123
Pa,
I want to thank you earlier

258
00:17:20,206 --> 00:17:21,791
for defending me from the media,

259
00:17:21,875 --> 00:17:23,460
but I can do this alone.

260
00:17:23,543 --> 00:17:24,878
Just stay put, Ace.

261
00:17:24,961 --> 00:17:26,379
I'm not done yet.

262
00:17:26,880 --> 00:17:29,716
Before the trial ends,
Teo will be destroyed.

263
00:17:31,551 --> 00:17:33,052
What are you doing here?

264
00:17:34,637 --> 00:17:37,474
You're trying to ruin me
because you're guilty.

265
00:17:37,557 --> 00:17:38,808
Oh?

266
00:17:38,892 --> 00:17:40,435
How is that ruining you?

267
00:17:40,518 --> 00:17:42,896
It's true you were jailed in Morocco.

268
00:17:43,396 --> 00:17:46,149
I was set up,
but I was granted a Royal Pardon.

269
00:17:46,232 --> 00:17:48,735
Even if you were granted a pardon,
you're still an ex-con.

270
00:17:48,818 --> 00:17:50,487
You were convicted, sentenced.

271
00:17:50,945 --> 00:17:53,782
Between you and me,
who will the court believe?

272
00:17:53,865 --> 00:17:56,701
Bring your wife out
so everyone will know the truth.

273
00:17:56,785 --> 00:17:58,036
Other people witnessed it.

274
00:17:58,119 --> 00:18:00,538
Why are you so confident
Gem will side with you?

275
00:18:02,123 --> 00:18:04,709
We'll block her if she tries to testify.

276
00:18:04,793 --> 00:18:08,630
She's Ace's wife.
She can't testify against the accused.

277
00:18:09,172 --> 00:18:11,007
Especially if it's proven

278
00:18:11,090 --> 00:18:13,468
you're just interfering
with their marriage.

279
00:18:14,010 --> 00:18:16,846
I should've killed you both
back then when I had the chance.

280
00:18:17,514 --> 00:18:19,641
I would've said I lost control.

281
00:18:19,724 --> 00:18:20,934
It was a crime of passion.

282
00:18:21,434 --> 00:18:22,519
Now tell me...

283
00:18:22,977 --> 00:18:24,979
did you sleep with my wife?

284
00:18:27,941 --> 00:18:29,609
I'll soon find out, Teo.

285
00:18:31,653 --> 00:18:32,821
Now leave.

286
00:18:40,829 --> 00:18:44,499
Alberto, do you have
an update on Mateo Crisanto?

287
00:18:44,582 --> 00:18:47,252
Yes, I checked
with my old office in Casablanca.

288
00:18:47,335 --> 00:18:50,255
I now know who submitted the list

289
00:18:50,338 --> 00:18:53,091
requesting the Royal Pardon
during that period.

290
00:18:54,092 --> 00:18:56,594
- <i>Go ahead.</i>
- My own nephew.

291
00:18:56,678 --> 00:18:58,847
<i>Your own son, Ace.</i>

292
00:19:02,725 --> 00:19:04,978
What did Ace do
when he went to Morocco?

293
00:19:05,478 --> 00:19:07,480
Who did he talk to? Who was he with?

294
00:19:07,564 --> 00:19:09,148
When, this year?

295
00:19:09,983 --> 00:19:12,944
I don't know.
We don't meet when he's there.

296
00:19:13,027 --> 00:19:14,904
About four years ago,
five years ago.

297
00:19:16,447 --> 00:19:19,701
I remember about three years ago,

298
00:19:19,784 --> 00:19:23,204
after going to Morocco, he went to Spain.

299
00:19:23,872 --> 00:19:26,040
That's where he met and married Gem.

300
00:19:27,292 --> 00:19:31,129
Pearl, do you have any details

301
00:19:31,212 --> 00:19:33,590
about Teo's accomplices in Morocco?

302
00:19:34,591 --> 00:19:36,092
Actually, none.

303
00:19:36,175 --> 00:19:38,511
I find it mysterious that I can't get

304
00:19:38,595 --> 00:19:40,513
any records of them in Morocco.

305
00:19:42,807 --> 00:19:46,561
Even on social media,
as if they don't exist.

306
00:19:46,644 --> 00:19:51,024
Maybe they're part of
a bigger network of thieves?

307
00:19:51,107 --> 00:19:53,526
No one is bigger than us, Pearl.

308
00:19:54,110 --> 00:19:58,531
Those people
have families, contacts, friends.

309
00:19:58,615 --> 00:20:00,742
We'll find them here in the Philippines.

310
00:20:24,891 --> 00:20:26,893
Don't do this to me, Ace.

311
00:20:26,976 --> 00:20:29,979
I'm not an animal.
Don't treat me like this.

312
00:20:30,563 --> 00:20:32,315
You don't want to be treated
like an animal?

313
00:20:32,982 --> 00:20:34,734
Then stop acting like one.

314
00:20:34,817 --> 00:20:36,444
You're the animal.

315
00:20:37,153 --> 00:20:39,572
You're worse than one.

316
00:20:39,906 --> 00:20:40,865
Let me go!

317
00:20:44,953 --> 00:20:46,371
Ace, wait!

318
00:20:46,454 --> 00:20:47,914
What did you say? Huh?

319
00:20:47,997 --> 00:20:49,248
Ace!

320
00:20:49,832 --> 00:20:51,834
- Ace, stop hurting her!
- Stay out of this!

321
00:20:52,293 --> 00:20:53,586
Ace!

322
00:20:53,670 --> 00:20:55,129
She's pregnant, stop!

323
00:20:55,213 --> 00:20:56,339
You're not leaving this room!

324
00:20:56,756 --> 00:20:58,508
- I said stop!
- What's going on here?

325
00:20:59,175 --> 00:21:00,927
You son of a bitch!

326
00:21:01,010 --> 00:21:02,011
That's your sister!

327
00:21:04,222 --> 00:21:05,223
Raya.

328
00:21:08,184 --> 00:21:11,020
Don't you lay a hand
on your sister ever again!

329
00:21:16,776 --> 00:21:19,362
Divino? Stop this!

330
00:21:19,445 --> 00:21:21,197
Divino, please stop it!

331
00:21:21,280 --> 00:21:23,616
- Stop!
- Not your sister!

332
00:21:24,701 --> 00:21:27,537
Lay a hand on her,
and you will regret it!

333
00:21:27,620 --> 00:21:29,330
Tell Raya to stop interfering!

334
00:21:29,414 --> 00:21:31,833
I'll talk to her, I promise!

335
00:21:31,916 --> 00:21:34,711
Stop tolerating your son!

336
00:21:34,794 --> 00:21:37,005
Why are you blaming me?

337
00:21:37,088 --> 00:21:38,756
Am I the only parent?

338
00:21:38,840 --> 00:21:41,300
Why don't you think about
your own shortcomings?

339
00:21:42,176 --> 00:21:43,594
This is all your fault!

340
00:21:44,762 --> 00:21:47,765
Alberto told me
you were the one who requested

341
00:21:47,849 --> 00:21:51,936
and submitted the list of Filipinos
for the Royal Pardon!

342
00:21:53,021 --> 00:21:53,855
Look!

343
00:21:58,735 --> 00:22:01,571
You asked for Mateo to be released!

344
00:22:03,031 --> 00:22:05,241
Why would you do this, Ace?

345
00:22:05,324 --> 00:22:06,701
Have you known him for a long time?

346
00:22:06,784 --> 00:22:09,203
She's been lying to me.
She's been with Teo for a long time.

347
00:22:09,287 --> 00:22:10,371
They both planned this!

348
00:22:12,498 --> 00:22:15,710
Enough for today.
You might kill her.

349
00:22:15,793 --> 00:22:18,463
Besides, she will not talk.

350
00:22:28,848 --> 00:22:30,016
Who's that?

351
00:22:30,808 --> 00:22:31,809
Who are you calling?

352
00:22:32,226 --> 00:22:33,269
Jorge.

353
00:22:34,187 --> 00:22:36,355
He's not answering his phone.

354
00:22:44,030 --> 00:22:45,865
- Raya?
- Ronnie?

355
00:22:45,948 --> 00:22:47,200
Are you crying?

356
00:22:47,825 --> 00:22:50,828
Ronnie, I've made up my mind.

357
00:22:52,413 --> 00:22:54,290
I want to help Gem escape.

358
00:22:54,791 --> 00:22:55,708
Why? What happened?

359
00:22:55,792 --> 00:22:57,752
Ace hurt me.

360
00:22:58,628 --> 00:22:59,712
What?

361
00:22:59,796 --> 00:23:01,380
<i>Ronnie, he's getting crazy.</i>

362
00:23:01,464 --> 00:23:04,175
Something might happen
to Gem and her baby.

363
00:23:04,258 --> 00:23:06,260
<i>I'm getting her out of here.</i>

364
00:23:06,344 --> 00:23:08,262
And I need your help.

365
00:23:09,555 --> 00:23:11,057
And Teo's.

366
00:23:11,140 --> 00:23:12,725
Okay, I'll tell him.

367
00:23:12,809 --> 00:23:14,060
Raya, be careful.

368
00:23:14,143 --> 00:23:16,229
Mm.

369
00:23:17,605 --> 00:23:18,481
What happened?

370
00:23:19,190 --> 00:23:20,441
Ace hurt Raya.

371
00:23:21,234 --> 00:23:23,486
She wants to help Gem
escape the mansion, too.

372
00:23:23,569 --> 00:23:25,071
Teo, let's help her.

373
00:23:25,154 --> 00:23:27,865
Tell her not to get involved.
I'll help Gem escape.

374
00:23:28,991 --> 00:23:31,077
Ronnie, Teo is right.

375
00:23:31,828 --> 00:23:32,912
She's still a Verona.

376
00:23:32,995 --> 00:23:35,039
She might back out at the last minute.

377
00:23:35,123 --> 00:23:36,999
Teo might get caught again.

378
00:23:37,083 --> 00:23:39,335
Pa, Raya can really help us.

379
00:23:39,418 --> 00:23:41,170
She's the only one in her family
with a conscience.

380
00:23:46,259 --> 00:23:48,386
You and Teo have been planning this
for a long time.

381
00:23:48,469 --> 00:23:49,971
What are you trying to do?

382
00:23:50,054 --> 00:23:51,097
What are you talking about?

383
00:23:51,180 --> 00:23:52,807
Teo's name is right here.
Don't play dumb.

384
00:23:52,890 --> 00:23:54,058
I didn't know.

385
00:23:54,517 --> 00:23:55,935
I told you before.

386
00:23:56,018 --> 00:23:58,646
The one I wanted pardoned
was Papa's colleague.

387
00:23:58,729 --> 00:24:00,398
Abegail Rodenas.

388
00:24:02,692 --> 00:24:04,193
She was a friend of mine.

389
00:24:05,653 --> 00:24:07,822
She was pregnant then,
that's why I asked you.

390
00:24:07,905 --> 00:24:09,824
But after her release, she died.

391
00:24:09,907 --> 00:24:11,159
You can't fool me.

392
00:24:11,242 --> 00:24:12,535
I'm not lying to you.

393
00:24:13,369 --> 00:24:14,620
It's written in there.

394
00:24:16,038 --> 00:24:17,623
Why would I make that up?

395
00:24:24,922 --> 00:24:26,257
I'm tired of this.

396
00:24:28,134 --> 00:24:29,927
I'm tired of fighting.

397
00:24:32,471 --> 00:24:35,474
We were fine before all this happened.

398
00:24:35,558 --> 00:24:37,810
- You caused it.
- I know.

399
00:24:40,354 --> 00:24:43,274
That's why I was up all night
just thinking.

400
00:24:47,820 --> 00:24:49,614
For our baby...

401
00:24:52,074 --> 00:24:54,577
Enough. I don't want to fight anymore.

402
00:24:57,455 --> 00:24:59,290
I just want to be a good wife.

403
00:25:01,209 --> 00:25:03,878
And a good mom to our baby.

404
00:25:30,780 --> 00:25:32,698
Ma'am, you might be hungry.

405
00:25:33,241 --> 00:25:34,575
Okay, just leave it there.

406
00:25:36,702 --> 00:25:38,537
Rica?

407
00:25:38,621 --> 00:25:39,705
Ma'am?

408
00:25:39,789 --> 00:25:41,874
Ace and I had a serious talk.

409
00:25:43,125 --> 00:25:44,252
That's good.

410
00:25:44,335 --> 00:25:48,172
I hope everything gets fixed
so the house can be at peace again.

411
00:25:48,256 --> 00:25:49,590
Soon.

412
00:25:53,344 --> 00:25:55,596
- Thank you.
- Okay, ma'am.

413
00:26:00,309 --> 00:26:03,562
Ma'am Gem, would you like
to get some fresh air?

414
00:26:03,646 --> 00:26:05,815
In the garden. Sir Ace told me to ask you.

415
00:26:05,898 --> 00:26:08,234
Later, I'll just eat first.

416
00:26:08,317 --> 00:26:09,568
Okay, ma'am.

417
00:26:38,180 --> 00:26:41,183
<i>Divino has been trying to contact me.</i>

418
00:26:41,267 --> 00:26:43,477
<i>He stated it's an urgent matter.</i>

419
00:26:43,561 --> 00:26:45,980
<i>Don't answer his calls, Jorge.</i>

420
00:26:46,063 --> 00:26:47,565
<i>I'll be the one to fix this.</i>

421
00:26:47,648 --> 00:26:48,899
All right.

422
00:27:08,794 --> 00:27:10,046
It's really good when it's cold.

423
00:27:10,129 --> 00:27:10,963
Excuse me.

424
00:27:11,672 --> 00:27:13,591
Where are the people who live there?

425
00:27:13,674 --> 00:27:15,926
Ah, they've been gone for a while.

426
00:27:16,677 --> 00:27:19,305
- Since when?
- About three weeks ago.

427
00:27:21,432 --> 00:27:22,725
Hello, Ronnie.

428
00:27:22,808 --> 00:27:24,769
There's another car watching the place.

429
00:27:24,852 --> 00:27:26,687
Maybe it's Leon again.

430
00:27:26,771 --> 00:27:28,230
Or maybe the Veronas.

431
00:27:28,314 --> 00:27:30,941
Don't leave Papa alone,
and don't go outside.

432
00:27:33,402 --> 00:27:35,071
Do you have their contact number?

433
00:27:35,154 --> 00:27:36,405
Who are you?

434
00:27:36,489 --> 00:27:37,823
Ah...

435
00:27:39,075 --> 00:27:41,494
Their aunt.

436
00:27:44,955 --> 00:27:48,000
I only have Issay's number.

437
00:27:48,084 --> 00:27:49,543
Give it to me.

438
00:27:50,294 --> 00:27:51,545
Give it to her.

439
00:27:59,011 --> 00:28:00,721
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

440
00:28:00,805 --> 00:28:02,056
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

441
00:28:19,573 --> 00:28:20,991
Let's go.

442
00:28:24,787 --> 00:28:25,830
Ma!

443
00:28:26,497 --> 00:28:27,540
Ma!

444
00:28:32,670 --> 00:28:33,754
<i>Are you sure, son?</i>

445
00:28:34,797 --> 00:28:36,715
Maybe you just imagined it.

446
00:28:36,799 --> 00:28:38,717
I'm sure, Pa. I saw her.

447
00:28:39,718 --> 00:28:40,553
Well...

448
00:28:42,138 --> 00:28:43,806
you said yourself

449
00:28:44,348 --> 00:28:47,435
that you saw
your mother's grave in Morocco.

450
00:28:47,518 --> 00:28:48,477
So she's already dead.

451
00:28:48,561 --> 00:28:51,480
Yeah, Teo.
Maybe she just looked like your mom.

452
00:28:52,064 --> 00:28:53,357
No, it was her.

453
00:28:53,441 --> 00:28:55,401
I saw her. She was in a nice car.

454
00:28:55,484 --> 00:28:57,319
I think she recognized me,
so she left right away.

455
00:28:57,403 --> 00:29:00,614
Son, you have too much
on your mind right now.

456
00:29:00,698 --> 00:29:02,700
That's why you're seeing things.

457
00:29:04,118 --> 00:29:06,912
Teo, I've spoken to Raya.

458
00:29:08,122 --> 00:29:10,207
- I told her.
- About our plan?

459
00:29:10,291 --> 00:29:11,292
No.

460
00:29:12,126 --> 00:29:14,128
But I couldn't stop her.

461
00:29:14,879 --> 00:29:17,715
If we don't want to do it,
she'll help Gem escape.

462
00:29:23,512 --> 00:29:24,513
Yes, Doc?

463
00:29:24,597 --> 00:29:26,307
Attorney Verona, hi!

464
00:29:26,390 --> 00:29:28,517
I'd like to schedule
a follow-up checkup with your wife.

465
00:29:28,601 --> 00:29:30,269
<i>Can I see her tomorrow?</i>

466
00:29:30,352 --> 00:29:32,104
Does she have an appointment?

467
00:29:32,188 --> 00:29:33,522
She didn't say anything to me.

468
00:29:33,606 --> 00:29:36,567
Uh, I told her
the last time she was in the clinic.

469
00:29:36,650 --> 00:29:43,157
I also want to give
the result of your paternal DNA test.

470
00:29:43,240 --> 00:29:44,492
<i>They're ready.</i>

471
00:29:45,159 --> 00:29:46,577
What time tomorrow?

472
00:29:46,660 --> 00:29:47,495
Ten o'clock.

473
00:29:47,578 --> 00:29:48,913
Okay, okay.

474
00:29:48,996 --> 00:29:51,123
We'll be there at 10:00. Thank you.

475
00:29:54,877 --> 00:29:57,838
Tomorrow's our chance
to get Gem out, at the hospital.

476
00:29:58,839 --> 00:30:00,424
She has a doctor's appointment.

477
00:30:00,508 --> 00:30:02,426
Okay, we'll handle it tomorrow, Raya.

478
00:30:02,510 --> 00:30:04,553
<i>No. I can help.</i>

479
00:30:04,637 --> 00:30:06,972
<i>And you can't do this alone.</i>

480
00:30:07,056 --> 00:30:08,390
I promise,

481
00:30:08,474 --> 00:30:11,644
they won't find out
we're helping Gem escape.

482
00:30:12,144 --> 00:30:13,979
And I have a plan.

483
00:30:20,277 --> 00:30:21,612
Teo!

484
00:30:21,695 --> 00:30:23,822
Hold up, Teo!

485
00:30:23,906 --> 00:30:27,076
I can take care of Issay.
Do you really have to take her?

486
00:30:27,159 --> 00:30:28,160
I do.

487
00:30:28,994 --> 00:30:31,747
I feel like
the world is closing in on us, Larajean.

488
00:30:32,498 --> 00:30:35,501
What if they find out
we're not really together?

489
00:30:35,584 --> 00:30:38,170
What if we stopped pretending?

490
00:30:40,965 --> 00:30:43,634
Where are you really going, Teo?

491
00:30:43,717 --> 00:30:45,886
Probably Papa's hometown.

492
00:30:45,970 --> 00:30:47,221
Who's going with you?

493
00:30:47,805 --> 00:30:50,266
Me, Issay, Papa, and Ronnie.

494
00:30:50,349 --> 00:30:51,350
And Gem?

495
00:30:57,565 --> 00:30:58,649
Wow.

496
00:30:59,733 --> 00:31:02,152
She has ruined your entire life.

497
00:31:03,320 --> 00:31:06,323
Are the paternity test results
out already?

498
00:31:06,407 --> 00:31:07,575
Are you the father of her child?

499
00:31:08,158 --> 00:31:09,910
Could you give us a moment, Issay?

500
00:31:12,913 --> 00:31:14,415
Answer me, Teo.

501
00:31:14,498 --> 00:31:15,666
I don't know.

502
00:31:15,749 --> 00:31:18,627
Whether I'm the father or not,
I'm still going to save her.

503
00:31:18,711 --> 00:31:19,962
Mm!

504
00:31:20,045 --> 00:31:22,798
So it hasn't been confirmed...

505
00:31:22,881 --> 00:31:24,967
...but you're still willing

506
00:31:25,050 --> 00:31:27,511
to go against the Veronas for her.

507
00:31:28,304 --> 00:31:29,513
Amazing!

508
00:31:29,597 --> 00:31:31,015
Is this what you really want?

509
00:31:31,599 --> 00:31:33,851
For you and your family
to always be on the run?

510
00:31:34,310 --> 00:31:35,227
Because of Gem?

511
00:31:35,686 --> 00:31:37,771
What is it with that woman?

512
00:31:37,855 --> 00:31:40,441
I can offer you peace and safety.

513
00:31:41,358 --> 00:31:44,987
Yes, I cheated on you back in Morocco,
but since then,

514
00:31:45,070 --> 00:31:48,574
I've made it my mission
to make it up to you.

515
00:31:48,657 --> 00:31:50,242
Just so you'll love me again.

516
00:31:50,326 --> 00:31:52,870
I spoke to ambassadors.

517
00:31:52,953 --> 00:31:55,581
I worked for the Veronas.
I pretended to be your girlfriend.

518
00:31:55,664 --> 00:31:58,751
I kept all your secrets! Each one of them.

519
00:32:00,127 --> 00:32:01,462
And it's still not enough?

520
00:32:02,630 --> 00:32:05,132
Sorry, Larajean.

521
00:32:05,924 --> 00:32:08,218
Thank you
for everything you've done for me.

522
00:32:08,302 --> 00:32:11,513
But I can't repay you.

523
00:32:12,931 --> 00:32:13,932
Screw you.

524
00:32:15,267 --> 00:32:16,310
Screw you!

525
00:32:18,520 --> 00:32:20,064
You bastard!

526
00:32:20,147 --> 00:32:21,231
Larajean!

527
00:32:34,953 --> 00:32:37,665
I'll speak to the client first.

528
00:32:37,748 --> 00:32:40,584
After that,
I'm going to make you speak to her.

529
00:32:40,668 --> 00:32:41,794
Impress her, okay?

530
00:32:45,673 --> 00:32:47,257
Are you sick or something?

531
00:32:47,341 --> 00:32:49,635
Um... uh... no, ma'am.

532
00:32:49,718 --> 00:32:50,928
Oh, my gosh!

533
00:32:51,011 --> 00:32:52,554
Have you been crying?

534
00:32:53,639 --> 00:32:56,225
Larajean, is this about that Teo guy?

535
00:32:57,935 --> 00:33:00,979
You are above him, Larajean.

536
00:33:01,063 --> 00:33:02,648
Choose better!

537
00:33:03,941 --> 00:33:07,027
I've moved on from him, ma'am.

538
00:33:07,695 --> 00:33:09,196
Well, good for you.

539
00:33:09,697 --> 00:33:12,366
Wait a minute. Where's my purse?

540
00:33:13,826 --> 00:33:16,245
Uh... oh, I'm sorry, ma'am.

541
00:33:16,328 --> 00:33:18,414
I'll go get it for you. I'm sorry.

542
00:33:18,497 --> 00:33:20,666
You see what this is doing to you?

543
00:33:20,749 --> 00:33:22,042
- Sorry.
- Hurry up.

544
00:33:23,001 --> 00:33:25,504
Oh, my goodness, Larajean.

545
00:33:26,004 --> 00:33:28,799
I don't know, of all people...

546
00:34:01,415 --> 00:34:02,458
Well?

547
00:34:03,834 --> 00:34:05,252
Hello, Katarina.

548
00:34:05,794 --> 00:34:07,296
You were with my husband?

549
00:34:07,379 --> 00:34:08,839
Don't make a scene.

550
00:34:08,922 --> 00:34:10,090
Look who's talking.

551
00:34:10,632 --> 00:34:13,886
If there's anything I hate,
it's a scandal.

552
00:34:13,969 --> 00:34:17,681
But your presence here?
That's the scandal.

553
00:34:17,765 --> 00:34:20,350
I was talking to an investor.

554
00:34:20,434 --> 00:34:22,352
If that's what you want to know.

555
00:34:22,436 --> 00:34:24,730
I don't want to know anything about you.

556
00:34:24,813 --> 00:34:27,107
Divino and I have an agreement.

557
00:34:27,191 --> 00:34:29,234
A memorandum of agreement.

558
00:34:29,318 --> 00:34:31,111
Didn't you receive a copy?

559
00:34:31,195 --> 00:34:32,905
Haven't you read the memo?

560
00:34:32,988 --> 00:34:34,490
Well, it states...

561
00:34:34,573 --> 00:34:37,743
...that you can't set foot
in this country.

562
00:34:38,786 --> 00:34:40,996
This is Divino's home.

563
00:34:41,789 --> 00:34:45,375
The turf of the spouse.

564
00:34:45,459 --> 00:34:46,877
The homemaker.

565
00:34:47,336 --> 00:34:49,296
The mother of his kids.

566
00:34:49,880 --> 00:34:52,549
And the legal wife.

567
00:35:00,599 --> 00:35:01,850
I have to go.

568
00:35:01,934 --> 00:35:04,311
I'm glad
you still have an ounce of shame in you.

569
00:35:07,815 --> 00:35:09,233
Thank you, thank you.

570
00:35:11,318 --> 00:35:12,402
Ma'am?

571
00:35:13,278 --> 00:35:14,321
Ma'am, your purse--

572
00:35:14,404 --> 00:35:15,781
Cancel my meeting.

573
00:35:15,864 --> 00:35:16,907
What?

574
00:35:16,990 --> 00:35:18,742
Cancel my meeting!

575
00:35:19,368 --> 00:35:21,453
Look for my husband!

576
00:35:27,251 --> 00:35:29,336
Guess who I just bumped into!

577
00:35:29,419 --> 00:35:30,754
I'm in the middle of a meeting.

578
00:35:30,838 --> 00:35:32,673
I don't care!

579
00:35:32,756 --> 00:35:35,676
Why should I even care
when you don't even give a damn?

580
00:35:36,593 --> 00:35:39,429
And I don't even care if Alberto hears it.

581
00:35:39,513 --> 00:35:42,349
He's my cousin! He's family.

582
00:35:42,432 --> 00:35:44,184
I have to go to the restroom.

583
00:35:44,852 --> 00:35:46,270
Let's talk about it at home.

584
00:35:46,353 --> 00:35:47,354
Divino, no!

585
00:35:48,313 --> 00:35:51,525
We agreed
that you wouldn't let your mistress

586
00:35:51,608 --> 00:35:53,026
come back to the Philippines.

587
00:35:53,110 --> 00:35:56,029
But she's out here parading herself!

588
00:35:56,113 --> 00:35:57,865
We agreed

589
00:35:58,365 --> 00:36:01,118
that she couldn't come back
to the Philippines!

590
00:36:01,451 --> 00:36:02,452
For what?

591
00:36:02,536 --> 00:36:04,162
For everyone to see?

592
00:36:04,246 --> 00:36:06,081
For all of my friends to know?

593
00:36:06,582 --> 00:36:09,418
I said we'll talk about this at home!

594
00:36:12,838 --> 00:36:14,923
- Larajean, let's go.
- Yes, madam.

595
00:36:15,007 --> 00:36:17,676
Wait a minute, madam.
I'm sorry. Hold on.

596
00:36:17,759 --> 00:36:19,761
- Let's go, Larajean.
- Divino.

597
00:36:19,845 --> 00:36:21,763
The girl who was with Katarina

598
00:36:21,847 --> 00:36:25,142
was the one who wanted to thank me
for Teo's release.

599
00:36:25,225 --> 00:36:26,143
What?

600
00:36:30,522 --> 00:36:31,565
Larajean.

601
00:36:34,151 --> 00:36:35,569
We need to talk.

602
00:36:40,490 --> 00:36:42,242
Where is the result of the DNA test, Doc?

603
00:36:42,326 --> 00:36:44,119
Someone will call you later.

604
00:36:44,202 --> 00:36:46,163
I just need to check on Gem first.

605
00:36:57,758 --> 00:36:58,800
Ah...

606
00:37:02,262 --> 00:37:04,097
Can you get that thing off her foot?

607
00:37:04,181 --> 00:37:05,515
Why?

608
00:37:05,599 --> 00:37:07,768
Your wife's foot is swollen.

609
00:37:08,268 --> 00:37:09,770
I'll just have it repositioned.

610
00:37:09,853 --> 00:37:13,106
It can't be done, Doc.
Just check her while it's there.

611
00:37:19,154 --> 00:37:20,197
Hello?

612
00:37:23,158 --> 00:37:24,743
Okay, I'll be there.

613
00:37:25,452 --> 00:37:26,787
What is it?

614
00:37:27,454 --> 00:37:29,289
The result of the paternity test
is now available.

615
00:37:29,373 --> 00:37:30,248
I'll just get it in the laboratory.

616
00:37:30,332 --> 00:37:31,917
- I'll come with you.
- No.

617
00:37:32,876 --> 00:37:35,379
The doctor is here,
and the guards are by the door.

618
00:37:35,462 --> 00:37:36,463
Just stay here.

619
00:37:41,343 --> 00:37:44,012
You're keeping something from us again.

620
00:37:45,847 --> 00:37:47,849
You know Attorney Alberto.

621
00:37:47,933 --> 00:37:50,102
He's a former attaché in Morocco.

622
00:37:50,185 --> 00:37:51,979
I remember you, dear.

623
00:37:52,062 --> 00:37:55,315
You thanked me for Teo's pardon.

624
00:37:55,399 --> 00:37:58,819
I also recall you saying
that you wrote to me.

625
00:38:01,947 --> 00:38:04,449
Is that true, Larajean?

626
00:38:07,577 --> 00:38:08,578
Yes, ma'am.

627
00:38:08,662 --> 00:38:10,831
You knew Mateo from before?

628
00:38:12,332 --> 00:38:13,500
Are you his accomplice?

629
00:38:13,583 --> 00:38:15,210
I checked your records.

630
00:38:15,293 --> 00:38:17,004
You worked in Morocco.

631
00:38:17,087 --> 00:38:19,339
At the same time that Teo worked there.

632
00:38:20,549 --> 00:38:21,800
Y-yes.

633
00:38:22,718 --> 00:38:24,386
Yes, I admit it, Judge.

634
00:38:24,469 --> 00:38:26,722
I've known Teo for a long time.

635
00:38:27,222 --> 00:38:30,225
In fact, we're childhood friends.

636
00:38:30,684 --> 00:38:34,271
We grew up together.
We chased our dreams together.

637
00:38:34,896 --> 00:38:39,151
He was my boyfriend
before I went to Morocco.

638
00:38:39,943 --> 00:38:44,031
But when I arrived there, I...

639
00:38:45,532 --> 00:38:47,117
I met someone else.

640
00:38:48,368 --> 00:38:50,287
I made a mistake.

641
00:38:50,370 --> 00:38:53,123
I chose someone with more money.

642
00:38:53,832 --> 00:38:55,751
But that was before.

643
00:38:55,834 --> 00:38:56,752
I flew back to the Philippines,

644
00:38:56,835 --> 00:38:59,755
hoping that I would be able
to make it up to him.

645
00:39:00,505 --> 00:39:02,924
That's why you're protecting him?

646
00:39:03,008 --> 00:39:04,718
You think he'll get back with you?

647
00:39:05,135 --> 00:39:06,219
Well...

648
00:39:07,220 --> 00:39:08,305
yes.

649
00:39:10,724 --> 00:39:11,850
And now...

650
00:39:14,436 --> 00:39:16,188
I've realized

651
00:39:16,772 --> 00:39:18,523
that I was so stupid.

652
00:39:18,607 --> 00:39:21,902
Because no matter what I do
to get him back,

653
00:39:21,985 --> 00:39:24,613
if he doesn't love me anymore,
I can't do anything about it.

654
00:39:24,696 --> 00:39:26,948
Were you involved
in the robbery in Marrakech?

655
00:39:28,575 --> 00:39:31,995
No, Judge. I wasn't. I'm not a thief.

656
00:39:32,079 --> 00:39:34,915
Even Teo... he's not a thief.

657
00:39:34,998 --> 00:39:36,374
He just got roped into it.

658
00:39:36,458 --> 00:39:38,960
He was jailed,
even though he was innocent.

659
00:39:39,044 --> 00:39:42,047
Because the real thief set him up.

660
00:39:44,341 --> 00:39:46,676
Who set him up?

661
00:39:47,677 --> 00:39:49,054
Is it Guillermo?

662
00:39:49,638 --> 00:39:50,680
Diane?

663
00:39:51,306 --> 00:39:52,557
Yana Kassir?

664
00:39:58,480 --> 00:39:59,815
It was Yana Kassir.

665
00:40:02,526 --> 00:40:04,361
She seduced Teo.

666
00:40:05,737 --> 00:40:07,072
She deceived him.

667
00:40:09,282 --> 00:40:10,408
And now...

668
00:40:12,661 --> 00:40:14,579
she's back in the Philippines.

669
00:40:14,663 --> 00:40:16,289
She's somewhere close to us,

670
00:40:17,082 --> 00:40:18,583
still deceiving people.

671
00:40:19,084 --> 00:40:21,461
She's trying to deceive Teo again.

672
00:40:21,545 --> 00:40:22,546
And deceive you, too.

673
00:40:23,922 --> 00:40:27,843
But... we don't know any Yana Kassir.

674
00:40:28,844 --> 00:40:30,929
Do you know her, Divino?

675
00:40:33,598 --> 00:40:35,100
Yana...

676
00:40:37,644 --> 00:40:39,938
is Ma'am Gem.

677
00:40:40,689 --> 00:40:41,606
What?

678
00:40:45,026 --> 00:40:47,445
She is Yana Kassir.

679
00:41:07,174 --> 00:41:08,508
Gem.

680
00:41:08,592 --> 00:41:10,343
You don't have to worry anymore.

681
00:41:10,427 --> 00:41:12,137
I was able to talk to your friend.

682
00:41:12,220 --> 00:41:13,972
She told me everything.

683
00:41:14,681 --> 00:41:16,850
Your husband is hurting you.

684
00:41:17,434 --> 00:41:19,603
And she asked me to help you.

685
00:41:20,478 --> 00:41:21,730
Who was it?

686
00:41:21,813 --> 00:41:22,814
Frida.

687
00:41:30,739 --> 00:41:31,990
She asked me to give this to you.

688
00:41:32,073 --> 00:41:33,325
Call her.

689
00:41:35,702 --> 00:41:36,912
Thank you.

690
00:41:39,998 --> 00:41:41,499
It's the boss.

691
00:41:43,043 --> 00:41:45,128
- Thank you.
- Be careful, okay?

692
00:41:54,387 --> 00:41:57,557
I'm just going to get the result
for Mrs. Verona from the lab.

693
00:41:57,641 --> 00:41:58,934
- I'll be back.
- Okay, Doc.

694
00:41:59,017 --> 00:42:00,060
All right.

695
00:42:20,038 --> 00:42:21,373
What's "cannot be excluded"?

696
00:42:21,456 --> 00:42:22,624
What does this mean?

697
00:42:22,707 --> 00:42:24,793
It's scientific language, sir.

698
00:42:25,293 --> 00:42:26,503
In DNA testing,

699
00:42:26,586 --> 00:42:30,715
one hundred percent is mathematically
impossible due to mutations.

700
00:42:30,799 --> 00:42:35,011
But 99.9% is legal and medical proof.

701
00:42:35,095 --> 00:42:36,805
There is no doubt that the child is yours.

702
00:42:36,888 --> 00:42:38,265
It's already sealed.

703
00:42:39,015 --> 00:42:41,601
- Doc, thank you.
- All right. Thank you.

704
00:42:46,648 --> 00:42:47,774
It's mine.

705
00:42:49,484 --> 00:42:51,319
The baby really is mine.

706
00:43:00,537 --> 00:43:01,371
Boss.

707
00:43:01,454 --> 00:43:02,914
Listen to me, Yana.

708
00:43:02,998 --> 00:43:05,834
In the clinic's exam room
near Dr. Casuga...

709
00:43:06,793 --> 00:43:09,170
<i>look for the second changing room.</i>

710
00:43:13,550 --> 00:43:16,469
<i>You need to open it</i>
<i>to reveal another door.</i>

711
00:43:16,553 --> 00:43:17,554
<i>You'll exit from there.</i>

712
00:43:23,685 --> 00:43:26,187
<i>That door will lead to another door</i>

713
00:43:26,271 --> 00:43:28,565
<i>that leads to the corridor at the back.</i>

714
00:43:28,648 --> 00:43:30,400
<i>Take the elevator.</i>

715
00:43:30,483 --> 00:43:31,985
<i>Then, I'll tell you what to do.</i>

716
00:43:54,299 --> 00:43:55,383
Raya?

717
00:44:01,681 --> 00:44:03,266
What are you doing here?

718
00:44:05,143 --> 00:44:06,644
- Gem, get inside, please.
- No.

719
00:44:06,728 --> 00:44:07,854
- Please!
- Raya, please.

720
00:44:07,937 --> 00:44:09,147
Don't get involved, please.

721
00:44:09,230 --> 00:44:11,399
We don't have time, and it's too late.

722
00:44:12,359 --> 00:44:13,568
Get inside!

723
00:44:57,112 --> 00:44:58,488
Are they still inside?

724
00:44:58,571 --> 00:45:00,990
She's been in there for a long time.

725
00:45:11,376 --> 00:45:12,794
Did you see her come out?

726
00:45:13,294 --> 00:45:15,463
We only saw the doctor come out
a while ago.

727
00:46:04,512 --> 00:46:05,555
Stay here, okay?

728
00:46:05,638 --> 00:46:09,684
You can't be seen.
I'll see if our car is already outside.

729
00:47:00,276 --> 00:47:02,946
Where's Yana?
She should be out here by now.

730
00:47:03,029 --> 00:47:06,032
I've been looking for her, ma'am.
But I still haven't seen her.

731
00:47:21,422 --> 00:47:22,257
Where's Gem?

732
00:47:22,340 --> 00:47:23,758
I'll go back inside for her.

733
00:47:25,176 --> 00:47:27,595
She's in the cart... as planned.

734
00:47:27,679 --> 00:47:28,888
I'll go.

735
00:48:10,847 --> 00:48:13,349
You can't hide me from my own blood, Gem.

736
00:48:13,433 --> 00:48:15,602
That baby is mine.

737
00:48:33,036 --> 00:48:34,662
That baby is mine!

738
00:48:55,433 --> 00:48:56,768
Gem!

739
00:48:57,352 --> 00:48:58,978
That demon Ace almost got me.

740
00:48:59,062 --> 00:49:00,480
- Are you okay?
- I'm okay.

741
00:49:00,563 --> 00:49:01,606
- Let's hurry.
- Come on.

742
00:49:29,550 --> 00:49:31,177
Sir, sir, sir! Please put that away.

743
00:49:31,260 --> 00:49:32,679
- We have patients here.
- Stay out of this.

744
00:49:32,762 --> 00:49:34,847
Sir, the patients might get scared.

745
00:49:37,350 --> 00:49:39,102
- Have you tracked them down?
- Here.

746
00:49:43,356 --> 00:49:44,941
- Where is this?
- Over here.

747
00:49:48,403 --> 00:49:49,570
Get the car!

748
00:49:53,533 --> 00:49:55,618
Sir! Sir, calm down.

749
00:49:55,702 --> 00:49:58,121
Sir! Sir! Sir! You can't do that.

750
00:49:59,580 --> 00:50:00,707
Let's go!

751
00:50:09,549 --> 00:50:10,466
Sir...

752
00:50:10,550 --> 00:50:11,551
Follow them.

753
00:50:26,649 --> 00:50:27,734
Please stop!

754
00:50:28,276 --> 00:50:29,485
Please don't hurt my brother!

755
00:50:29,569 --> 00:50:31,112
Gem!

756
00:50:31,779 --> 00:50:34,198
If we don't fight back,
we'll end up getting killed by Ace!

757
00:50:40,830 --> 00:50:41,998
Pull over!

758
00:50:42,081 --> 00:50:43,332
Huh? Ronnie, don't pull over!

759
00:50:53,176 --> 00:50:54,719
Teo, come back here!

760
00:50:54,802 --> 00:50:56,429
- Get in the car!
- Just wait for my call!

761
00:50:56,512 --> 00:50:58,347
- Teo, let's go!
- We're not leaving you here!

762
00:51:00,475 --> 00:51:02,435
Teo! Teo!

763
00:51:17,325 --> 00:51:18,367
Teo!

764
00:51:19,327 --> 00:51:20,244
Get in! Hurry!

765
00:51:27,543 --> 00:51:28,544
Please!

766
00:51:35,426 --> 00:51:36,385
No!

767
00:51:39,639 --> 00:51:43,392
Why didn't you tell me right away
that you knew who Gem was?

768
00:51:44,519 --> 00:51:47,605
You even knew
about her criminal background!

769
00:51:47,688 --> 00:51:51,275
Ma'am, you see, I didn't know at first.

770
00:51:51,984 --> 00:51:53,319
How did you know, then?

771
00:51:54,278 --> 00:51:56,447
Who told you about that? Was it Teo?

772
00:51:56,531 --> 00:51:58,783
So, you're in collusion with him!

773
00:51:58,866 --> 00:52:00,535
No, Judge.

774
00:52:01,327 --> 00:52:03,955
I had long been suspecting
that she was Yana,

775
00:52:04,038 --> 00:52:06,082
but Teo denied it to me.

776
00:52:06,165 --> 00:52:09,126
So, how did you know that Gem was Yana?

777
00:52:09,210 --> 00:52:11,003
I heard it from Gem herself.

778
00:52:11,087 --> 00:52:14,382
I confronted her,
and she admitted it to me.

779
00:52:14,465 --> 00:52:17,927
She also threatened me.
That's why I couldn't tell you right away.

780
00:52:24,016 --> 00:52:24,851
Ace.

781
00:52:24,934 --> 00:52:25,977
Pa, Gem got away.

782
00:52:26,060 --> 00:52:27,353
She's with Teo. They escaped!

783
00:52:27,436 --> 00:52:28,896
Go home.

784
00:52:28,980 --> 00:52:30,648
I'll look for Gem, Pa.

785
00:52:30,731 --> 00:52:32,108
Send me a car and some of our guys now.

786
00:52:32,191 --> 00:52:34,026
Go home first.

787
00:52:34,110 --> 00:52:36,112
Let that good-for-nothing woman go!

788
00:52:36,195 --> 00:52:38,114
I can't,
because she's pregnant with my child!

789
00:52:38,197 --> 00:52:39,282
It's mine, Pa!

790
00:52:39,365 --> 00:52:42,243
We will get her,
but we need to talk first.

791
00:52:46,956 --> 00:52:48,875
Gem ran away with Teo.

792
00:52:48,958 --> 00:52:50,084
What?

793
00:52:50,167 --> 00:52:52,211
Because you didn't speak up sooner,

794
00:52:52,295 --> 00:52:54,505
they managed to run away
with Ace's future child.

795
00:52:57,216 --> 00:53:00,052
You freaking liar!

796
00:53:00,136 --> 00:53:02,471
I gave you my trust, you traitor!

797
00:53:02,555 --> 00:53:05,057
No, madam!
It's not like that!

798
00:53:05,141 --> 00:53:07,310
- I was too scared to speak...
- Shut up!

799
00:53:07,393 --> 00:53:09,270
...but I'm not a traitor, ma'am!

800
00:53:09,353 --> 00:53:11,772
- Leave!
- I'll help you find them!

801
00:53:11,856 --> 00:53:14,150
I don't want
to see your face here ever again!

802
00:53:14,233 --> 00:53:16,611
But ma'am, Teo still trusts me.

803
00:53:16,694 --> 00:53:18,029
I'll bring him back.

804
00:53:18,112 --> 00:53:20,573
I'll bring Gem back.
I'll bring them to you.

805
00:53:34,879 --> 00:53:37,548
Ronnie, what are you doing?

806
00:53:39,383 --> 00:53:40,384
Boss?

807
00:53:41,677 --> 00:53:42,929
Teo's with me.

808
00:53:44,722 --> 00:53:46,390
He's safe.

809
00:53:46,474 --> 00:53:48,643
C-Copy, Boss.

810
00:54:05,660 --> 00:54:07,161
Teo, my son...

811
00:54:12,583 --> 00:54:13,918
What are you doing here?

812
00:54:18,005 --> 00:54:19,840
And why--

813
00:54:19,924 --> 00:54:21,258
why did you save me?

814
00:54:22,843 --> 00:54:24,345
You're supposed to be dead, right?

815
00:54:28,599 --> 00:54:29,767
Stop the car.

816
00:54:35,690 --> 00:54:37,108
Stop the car!

817
00:54:37,191 --> 00:54:38,275
- Y-Yes.
- Teo.

818
00:54:42,071 --> 00:54:43,114
Teo...

819
00:54:49,453 --> 00:54:50,663
Open the door, please.

820
00:54:55,209 --> 00:54:56,961
If it was your grave I saw before,

821
00:54:57,044 --> 00:54:58,295
then how are you alive?

822
00:55:01,716 --> 00:55:03,259
I've seen your grave in Morocco.

823
00:55:03,342 --> 00:55:05,928
We both saw your grave in Morocco,
Gem and I!

824
00:55:06,012 --> 00:55:08,764
So what was that? Huh?

825
00:55:10,433 --> 00:55:13,352
I'm not wrong.
I saw it clearly with my own eyes.

826
00:55:16,188 --> 00:55:17,189
What?

827
00:55:17,273 --> 00:55:19,650
Are you just going to stare at me?
Explain yourself!

828
00:55:20,276 --> 00:55:21,861
What's so hard about that?

829
00:55:24,947 --> 00:55:27,616
Did you do something foolish again?
Are you concealing a secret again?

830
00:55:30,327 --> 00:55:32,830
Is that why even your death
is all made up?

831
00:55:35,458 --> 00:55:36,709
Tell me!

832
00:55:51,265 --> 00:55:52,099
Gem, where are you?

833
00:55:52,600 --> 00:55:54,935
We stopped here in San Martin.

834
00:55:55,019 --> 00:55:56,812
Why did you stop? You have to get going!

835
00:55:56,896 --> 00:55:58,898
We want to know how you're doing.

836
00:55:59,190 --> 00:56:01,192
- Have the two of you left?
<i>- The two of us?</i>

837
00:56:01,275 --> 00:56:02,860
How did you know I'm with someone?

838
00:56:05,780 --> 00:56:09,450
You didn't even ask how I am,
if I'm still alive, or if I'm safe.

839
00:56:10,117 --> 00:56:11,118
Do you know something?

840
00:56:12,286 --> 00:56:13,704
I know you're safe.

841
00:56:14,288 --> 00:56:15,372
How?

842
00:56:18,292 --> 00:56:19,376
Don't tell me...

843
00:56:24,548 --> 00:56:27,802
Gem, I'm with my mom,
the one whose grave we visited in Morocco.

844
00:56:28,469 --> 00:56:29,553
I know.

845
00:56:30,096 --> 00:56:32,181
What do you mean you know?

846
00:56:32,264 --> 00:56:34,225
Have you known her for a long time?

847
00:56:34,308 --> 00:56:36,018
Teo, don't blame Yana.

848
00:56:41,607 --> 00:56:43,109
How do you know Yana?

849
00:56:44,860 --> 00:56:45,778
Huh?

850
00:56:47,196 --> 00:56:49,073
You've been fooling me for a long time.

851
00:56:49,949 --> 00:56:51,951
And even now, you're still fooling me?

852
00:56:54,078 --> 00:56:55,579
<i>Teo, I'm sorry.</i>

853
00:56:55,663 --> 00:56:57,665
I'll explain everything.

854
00:57:12,763 --> 00:57:13,764
Pa, Mama's alive.

855
00:57:13,848 --> 00:57:16,058
<i>You really have no shame, do you?</i>

856
00:57:16,142 --> 00:57:18,561
- Know your place.
- You want to know my place?

857
00:57:18,644 --> 00:57:19,979
My place is in his heart.

858
00:57:20,062 --> 00:57:21,605
<i>Damn you, Divino!</i>

859
00:57:22,439 --> 00:57:24,817
<i>Oh, my gosh! I know her, ma'am!</i>

860
00:57:24,900 --> 00:57:27,319
- That's Miss Rita.
- Who the hell is Rita?

861
00:57:28,362 --> 00:57:30,865
<i>We've known each other for a long time.</i>

862
00:57:30,948 --> 00:57:32,658
- Why didn't you tell me?
- Because if the Veronas know

863
00:57:32,741 --> 00:57:35,202
that you are her son,
Divino will kill you.

864
00:57:35,286 --> 00:57:37,371
A punishment worse than death.
